  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study the investigators wish to compare the effect of a selective axillary nerve
      block to placebo in patients undergoing arthroscopic shoulder surgery.

      It is the investigators hypothesis that the amount of morphine consumption in the first 4
      hours postoperatively in the intervention group will be significant lower than in the placebo
      group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
